OL,6,FShe said both parents put their
OL,7,Fdaughter in the role of a "sick and
OL,8,Fdisabled child, missing out on
OL,9,Fordinary childhood".JThe girl was put
OL,10,Fthrough "unnecessary medical
OL,11,Fprocedures" and given medication,
OL,12,Fincluding ibuprofen and paracetamol
OL,13,Fshe did not need.J"Some of this was to
OL,14,Fobtain enhanced welfare payments," Mrs
OL,15,FReevell said.JConcerns were raised by
OL,16,Fsocial services and medical
OL,17,Fprofessionals that the Laws were
OL,18,F"fabricating or exaggerating" the
OL,19,Fgirl's symptoms.
