OL,6,FThe victim was interviewed in
OL,7,FSeptember 2022, at the age of 18, when
OL,8,Fshe said that the behaviour from her
OL,9,Fparents started when she was aged five
OL,10,For six.J"Her parents would tell her
OL,11,Fwhat to say to the doctors or her
OL,12,Fparents would do the talking for her,"
OL,13,Fsaid Mrs Reevell.JThe Laws' home was
OL,14,Fadapted with grab rails and the family
OL,15,Falso received a car for the girl, paid
OL,16,Ffor out of mobility benefit.J"Her
OL,17,Fparents made her think that she could
OL,18,Fnot walk properly," Mrs Reevell said.
OL,19,F"She would go to school in a
OL,20,Fwheelchair but she didn't really need
OL,21,Fit."
