OL,6,F"She realised that she could do all
OL,7,Fthe things that her parents had told
OL,8,Fher that she could not."JIn a
OL,9,Fstatement, the girl said she was
OL,10,F"subjected to bullying" due to the
OL,11,Fwheelchair.
OL,13,F"I missed out on doing PE. I missed
OL,14,Fout on doing the normal things that
OL,15,Fother boys and girls were doing at
OL,16,Fbreak time," she said.J"The wheelchair
OL,17,Fbecame a barrier to mak(ing)
OL,18,Frelationships and friendships."
